    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/901a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-28T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confidential. In accordance request Liberian Government contained in last
                    paragraph your November 29, 5 p.m., Department will await receipt of full
                    written explanation, which it is assumed is now coming forward by mail.
                    Meanwhile on basis information contained in your November 29 and in accordance
                    with policy outlined in Department’s November 26 [<hi rend="italic">29?</hi>],
                    Department agrees with attitude of Liberian Government in declining to settle
                    matter in advance Peace Conference and settlement negotiations with British and
                    French Governments regarding refunding of loan of 1912.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
